Sometimes order flips (Australia vs Oman vs Oman vs Australia).

Use this instead:

(By.XPATH, "//a[contains(@href,'oman-vs-aus')]")
👍 Production-grade version
match = wait.until(
    EC.element_to_be_clickable(
        (By.XPATH, "//a[contains(@href,'oman-vs-aus')]")
    )
)
✅ Most stable
✅ Works even if title changes
✅ Survives UI redesign

🚨 If click fails (very common on Cricbuzz)
Because of carousel/overlay, use JS click:

driver.execute_script("arguments[0].click();", match)
🧪 Debug tip (pro level)
Before clicking, print what Selenium found:

print(match.get_attribute("title"))
